</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,1274,1769]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,281,1382,1408]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">Habitat</emphasis>
:—This species was found associated with periphyton of 
<taxonomicName box="[903,1111,1382,1408]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lentibulariaceae" genus="Utricularia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="foliosa">
<emphasis box="[903,1111,1382,1408]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">Utricularia foliosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. Gray" authorityYear="1837" box="[1161,1404,1382,1408]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cabombaceae" genus="Cabomba" kingdom="Plantae" order="Nymphaeales" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caroliniana">
<emphasis box="[1161,1404,1382,1408]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">Cabomba caroliniana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. EC 0.02 (± 0.01 mS 
<superScript attach="left" box="[322,369,1418,1445]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">cm-1</superScript>
), 
<collectionCode box="[392,432,1418,1444]" country="France" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14073" name="Société d'Agriculture Sciences et Arts" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" type="Herbarium">DO</collectionCode>
6.3 (± 
<quantity box="[511,589,1418,1445]" metricMagnitude="-7" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="3.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" unit="mg" value="0.3">0.3 mg</quantity>
L- 
<superScript attach="right" box="[618,625,1418,1432]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">1</superScript>
), pH 7.5 (± 0.8), TDS 0.01 (± 0.005), 
<collectionCode box="[1049,1066,1419,1445]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">T</collectionCode>
29.8 (± 1.8 ºC), WT 0.6 (± 
<quantity box="[1371,1444,1418,1444]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7999999999999998" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" unit="m" value="0.18">0.18m</quantity>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,1274,1769]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,245,1454,1480]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">Note</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName box="[281,542,1455,1481]" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" genus="Cosmarium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" phylum="Charophyta" rank="species" species="pygmaeum">
<emphasis box="[281,542,1455,1481]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">Cosmarium pygmaeum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a species with cosmopolitan distribution, with a bunch of records mainly in Europe (
<bibRefCitation author="Guiry, M. D. &amp; Guiry, G. M." box="[233,474,1490,1516]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" refId="ref4867" refString="Guiry, M. D. &amp; Guiry, G. M. (2020) AlgaeBase. World-wide electronic publication, National University of Ireland, Galway. Available from: http: // www. algaebase. org (accessed 19 December 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Guiry &amp; Guiry 2020</bibRefCitation>
). However, in 
<collectingCountry box="[642,710,1490,1516]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and even in South America, this species is rarely reported in the literature. There is only a record of its occurrence in the Brazilian territory, which was based on the sample gathered in municipality of Rio Claro, State of 
<collectingRegion box="[574,689,1562,1588]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
(Bicudo 1969, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bicudo, C. E. M. &amp; Araujo, A. &amp; Biolo, S." box="[869,1087,1562,1588]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" refId="ref4481" refString="Bicudo, C. E. M., Araujo, A. &amp; Biolo, S. (2019) Flora Ficologica do Estado de Sao Paulo. Parte 3: Zygnematophyceae 1. ed. Vol. 4. RiMa Editora, Sao Paulo, pp. 1 - 309." type="book" year="2019">
Bicudo 
<emphasis box="[959,1017,1562,1588]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
). Thus, the material from 
<collectingRegion box="[1386,1451,1562,1588]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">Bahia</collectingRegion>
represents the second record of that species in 
<collectingCountry box="[643,715,1598,1624]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. Overall, it is one of the most polymorphic and smaller 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Corda ex Ralfs" authorityYear="1848" box="[1321,1452,1599,1625]" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" genus="Cosmarium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" phylum="Charophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1321,1452,1599,1625]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">Cosmarium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
taxa occurring in the Marimbus. The main morphological variations in the specimens from 
<collectingRegion box="[1168,1233,1634,1660]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">Bahia</collectingRegion>
are the sinus, from open to closed, the central granule which can be next to the apical margin or close to the isthmus, and the papillae at the basal angles, which could be more or less projected (
<figureCitation box="[718,785,1706,1733]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="2.[136,243,2002,2024]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,278,1974]" captionTargetId="figure-69@2.[178,1409,278,1974]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Line drawings. 1. Cosmarium boeckii var.areolatum 2. C. clepsydra var. incrassatum 3. C. heptangulare 4. C. kanetsunae 5. C. pygmaeum 6. C. trinodulum 7. C. trinodulum var. brasiliense 8. C. trinodulum var. pilgeri." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5420998" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5420998/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Kouwets, F. A. C." box="[955,1135,1706,1733]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" pagination="193 - 263" refId="ref5012" refString="Kouwets, F. A. C. (1987) Desmids from the Auvergne (France). Hydrobiologia 146: 193 - 263. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / BF 00016347" type="journal article" year="1987">Kouwets (1987)</bibRefCitation>
the arrangement of granules on the cell wall is very variable, and without any taxonomic value.
</paragraph>
